# Plan Creation Guide

This guide helps you create structured plans using a standardized template format.

## Summary progress
- PlanA: 30% - 3/10
- PlanB: ...

## When to Use This Guide

Use this guide when you need to:
- Plan new features or improvements
- Document implementation steps
- Create structured task breakdowns
- Organize complex development work

## Best Practices

### Writing Effective Steps
- Start each step with an action verb (Create, Implement, Test, etc.)
- Be specific about what needs to be done
- Include acceptance criteria when helpful
- Consider dependencies between steps

### Naming Conventions
- Use descriptive filenames: `feature_name_plan.md`
- Place plans in `.docs/plan/` directory
- Use snake-case for filenames

### Plan Maintenance
- Update checkboxes and progress indicator as steps are completed
- Add new steps if scope changes
- Reference completed plans in new related work

## Example Usage

```markdown
# Plan Template

## Short Description
